crates/ctx-summarize/src is the `ctx-summarize` binary: it walks a set of repo-relative source paths, generates leaf `.ctx` summaries via an LLM agent, then rolls those up bottom-up into `rollup.ctx` files, emitting the resulting summary JSON on stdout.

Layering is strict and load-bearing: `main.rs` wires real dependencies (StdFs, SubprocessAgent) and calls `cli::dispatch`, which does argv parsing plus a scope-size gate (`scope_check`) before calling `runner::run` — all actual orchestration logic lives in `runner.rs`; `cli.rs` and `main.rs` must stay thin. `runner.rs` depends only on the `Fs` (fs.rs) and `Agent` (agent.rs) trait seams, both of which have testable in-memory/alternate implementations, and on `cpath.rs` for all `.context` mirror-path computation and `error.rs` for the shared `SummError` enum used across every fallible operation.

Two cross-cutting contracts editors must preserve: (1) the `--- label ---` section format `runner::assemble_rollup_input`/`push_section` produces is exactly what the rollup prompt sees for every child — changing it changes rollup quality tree-wide; (2) `cpath.rs`'s path-safety and `.context` mirror logic is deliberately duplicated in `ctx-context` (tracked in `docs/UNIMPLEMENTED.md`), so path-rule changes here need checking there too. Prompts are always loaded from files (`prompts/summarizer-leaf.md`, `summarizer-rollup.md`), never embedded as code constants — adding a prompt means adding a file. `intent.md` is read by rollups but never written by this crate anywhere in the pipeline.

Rollup ordering is a subtree-spanning invariant: `runner::affected_dirs` guarantees a directory's rollup only runs after all affected descendants' rollups (via strictly-decreasing depth), though sibling order at equal depth is unspecified. `fs::scope_matcher` (gitignore-syntax, `.ctxignore`-based, always ignoring `target/`) is the single scope definition shared with `ctx-scan`'s walker — keep them in sync. `agent.rs`'s subprocess wire contract (`{"system","user"}` JSON in, raw text out) is the only model-agnostic boundary; any `CTX_AGENT_CMD` script must match it.